From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: VyOS LS1046A maintainers <dpaa1@vyos-ls1046a-build>
Date: Fri, 29 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fman: add PCD KeyGen exact-match scheme API (common, all
 flavors)

Forward-port of the FMan PCD KeyGen layer from the ask20 branch into the
COMMON board patch stack (built-in for default/vpp/ask via the
FSL_FMAN_PCD config from patch 0092). Combines the ask20 0005
(KeyGen public API + struct/helper promotion) and 0006 (KeyGen
silicon-programming body) patches into a single re-anchored commit
against 6.18.31. This is PR2 of the dpaa1 PCD forward-port closing
M3-3b/M3-3c/M3-3d.

What this adds
--------------
- fman_keygen.c: promotes the previously file-static struct keygen_scheme
  and struct fman_keygen to a new module-internal header
  fman_keygen_internal.h, and demotes keygen_scheme_setup() /
  keygen_bind_port_to_schemes() from file-static to EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL so a
  sibling translation unit can populate a scheme slot (match_vector != 0)
  before delegating the KGSE_* register write to these existing helpers.
  No silicon behaviour change for the existing RSS-hashing path
  (keygen_port_hashing_init() etc.) - only linkage of two helpers changed.

- fman_pcd_kg.c (new, ~399 LOC): the public KeyGen API.
  fman_pcd_kg_scheme_create() allocates a free scheme id, builds the
  KGSE_MV match-vector for the canonical IPv4 5-tuple shape (SIP/DIP/proto/
  SPORT/DPORT via parse-result offsets 12/16/9/20/22, silicon bit values
  per RM 8.7.4 KGSE_MV), populates keygen->schemes[id], and calls the
  promoted keygen_scheme_setup() helper. fman_pcd_kg_bind_port() wires the
  port-binding AR register via keygen_bind_port_to_schemes().
  fman_pcd_kg_scheme_destroy() unbinds, disables, unlinks and frees.
  fman_pcd_kg_attach_cc() is intentionally still -EOPNOTSUPP: the KGSE_CCBS
  wiring depends on the CC tree subsystem (struct fman_pcd_cc_tree) which
  lands in a follow-up PCD patch.

- include/linux/fsl/fman_pcd.h: appends the public KG surface
  (enum fman_pcd_kg_extract_from, struct fman_pcd_kg_extract_spec,
  struct fman_pcd_kg_scheme_params, and the four entry points). All four
  entry points are EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL.

- Makefile: adds fman_pcd_kg.o to the FSL_FMAN_PCD object list.

The KG_SCH_KN_* match-vector bit constants are PRIVATE to fman_keygen.c
upstream (defined inline, not exported in any header); they are
replicated locally in fman_pcd_kg.c with the RM 8.7.4 KGSE_MV register
citation as the silicon-fact source. The supported match-vector shape at
this iteration is IPv4 5-tuple only; wider shapes (IPv6/MPLS/IPSEC)
return -EOPNOTSUPP loudly and extend kg_build_match_vector() in a
follow-up.

Signed-off-by: VyOS LS1046A maintainers <dpaa1@vyos-ls1046a-build>
---
